        <p> {{ page.overview.intro|raw }} the Elbe literally fell into the water. We decided to ignore the alarm clock, slept in and had breakfast in peace, while the rain drummed steadily on the roof. </p>
        <p> After the cozy start to the day, we checked out and parked our motorhome in the parking lot in front of the campsite. Thanks to the guest card, we were able to take the bus into downtown Pirna free of charge - an offer we were happy to use. </p>
        <p> The old town of Pirna surprised us with its charm. The small streets, historical facades and nicely decorated shop windows invited us to stroll, and we discovered sayings on various shop windows. We particularly liked the saying in the windows of a bakery café - on one window it said: "I'm so full, I don't want any Bla...", followed by the next window with "Oh, cake." Small details that stay in your memory. </p>
        <p> At the market square, we discovered a restaurant with a pleasant atmosphere and good music. Although the menu appealed to us directly, we were still too full from breakfast, so we decided to come back later. Instead, we continued to drift and finally ended up in a fabric shop. Actually, we just wanted to look in - in the end, we left with three meters of fabric in two colors. The planned sofa cushions at home can finally go into production. </p>

